<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Gulab Jamun Sweet</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup Gulab Jamun mix</li>
            <li>1/4 cup milk</li>
            <li>Oil or ghee for frying</li>
            <li>1 cup sugar</li>
            <li>1/2 cup water</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cardamom powder</li>
            <li>Chopped pistachios for garnish (optional)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>sweet</li>
            <li>dessert</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine Gulab Jamun mix and milk. Knead the mixture into a soft dough.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into small portions and shape them into round balls.</li>
            <li>Heat oil or ghee in a pan over medium heat. Fry the Gulab Jamun balls until golden brown and cooked through. Drain excess oil and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a separate saucepan, combine sugar and water to make a sugar syrup. Add cardamom powder and bring the syrup to a boil. Simmer for a few minutes until it slightly thickens.</li>
            <li>Soak the fried Gulab Jamun balls in the sugar syrup for at least 1-2 hours to allow them to absorb the sweetness.</li>
            <li>Garnish with chopped pistachios if desired.</li>
            <li>Serve and enjoy the delicious Gulab Jamun Sweet!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
